WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.930 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.930 --> 00:00:16.079 align:middle line:90%
>> My name is Raymond Moody.

00:00:16.079 --> 00:00:19.760 align:middle line:84%
I got a PhD in philosophy from
the University of Virginia.

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:23.540 align:middle line:84%
Then I went to medical school
and became a psychiatrist.

00:00:23.540 --> 00:00:26.410 align:middle line:84%
And I was 18 years
old when I found out

00:00:26.410 --> 00:00:28.130 align:middle line:90%
about near-death experiences.

00:00:28.130 --> 00:00:32.140 align:middle line:84%
And immediately, it was just
a fascinating concept to me.

00:00:32.140 --> 00:00:36.160 align:middle line:84%
I never had any thoughts
about life after death,

00:00:36.160 --> 00:00:40.000 align:middle line:84%
but I was astonished
that every place I ever

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.780 align:middle line:84%
went there were almost the
same things like, Dr. Moody,

00:00:43.780 --> 00:00:46.360 align:middle line:84%
I've never told
anybody this, but--

00:00:46.360 --> 00:00:50.470 align:middle line:84%
and I quickly realized that it
was a very common phenomenon.

00:00:50.470 --> 00:00:55.600 align:middle line:84%
And it inspired me in the
career that I had subsequently

00:00:55.600 --> 00:00:59.560 align:middle line:84%
of being able to interview
literally thousands of people

00:00:59.560 --> 00:01:03.220 align:middle line:84%
from all over the world
who had these experiences.

00:01:03.220 --> 00:01:08.230 align:middle line:84%
And so my first book, which
was published in 1975,

00:01:08.230 --> 00:01:11.770 align:middle line:84%
was entitled Life
After Life, but I just

00:01:11.770 --> 00:01:16.160 align:middle line:84%
had no idea that it was going to
create the worldwide sensation

00:01:16.160 --> 00:01:17.100 align:middle line:90%
it did.

00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:18.920 align:middle line:84%
What I think
happened, by the way,

00:01:18.920 --> 00:01:24.860 align:middle line:84%
was by the 1960s and '70s, when
I was starting to investigate

00:01:24.860 --> 00:01:29.180 align:middle line:84%
this, by that time, due to
the advent of cardiopulmonary

00:01:29.180 --> 00:01:33.860 align:middle line:84%
resuscitation, it was just so
common for people to be brought

00:01:33.860 --> 00:01:39.860 align:middle line:84%
back, whereas for eons before
then, it was a very rare event.

00:01:39.860 --> 00:01:43.940 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm Eben Alexander, MD, and
I had a profound near-death

00:01:43.940 --> 00:01:45.900 align:middle line:90%
experience back in 2008.

00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:49.220 align:middle line:84%
Before that time, I was
a conventionally trained

00:01:49.220 --> 00:01:51.350 align:middle line:90%
neurosurgeon of the modern era.

00:01:51.350 --> 00:01:55.130 align:middle line:84%
And my academic career, I
trained at Duke Medical Center.

00:01:55.130 --> 00:01:57.620 align:middle line:10%
And then was up at Harvard
Medical School, where

00:01:57.620 --> 00:02:01.640 align:middle line:10%
I taught for more than 15
years, which means I basically

00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:05.090 align:middle line:10%
had been trained fully in
materialism or physicalism,

00:02:05.090 --> 00:02:07.430 align:middle line:10%
the notion that only the
physical world exists,

00:02:07.430 --> 00:02:10.009 align:middle line:10%
and that if we understand
all the laws governing

00:02:10.009 --> 00:02:13.760 align:middle line:10%
the workings of that world,
we understand all of reality.

00:02:13.760 --> 00:02:17.330 align:middle line:84%
And then in November 2008,
I had a profound experience

00:02:17.330 --> 00:02:20.450 align:middle line:84%
that showed me that that
model was flat out incorrect

00:02:20.450 --> 00:02:22.580 align:middle line:84%
and that there's
much more going on

00:02:22.580 --> 00:02:25.040 align:middle line:84%
to this mind-brain
relationship than I ever

00:02:25.040 --> 00:02:27.230 align:middle line:90%
would have surmised before.

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:29.270 align:middle line:84%
And I think that was
probably the greatest

00:02:29.270 --> 00:02:31.580 align:middle line:84%
gift of my near-death
experience,

00:02:31.580 --> 00:02:36.780 align:middle line:84%
was finding a world that I
completely did not expect,

00:02:36.780 --> 00:02:39.170 align:middle line:84%
and yet it seemed
like a spiritual home.

00:02:39.170 --> 00:02:44.000 align:middle line:84%
And in many ways, it was far
more real than this world.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:46.490 align:middle line:84%
I did not anticipate
that in any way,

00:02:46.490 --> 00:02:48.150 align:middle line:84%
and yet that's
what I experienced.

00:02:48.150 --> 00:02:52.220 align:middle line:84%
And especially given the
medical parameters of my case,

00:02:52.220 --> 00:02:54.980 align:middle line:84%
you realize that
brain of mine was

00:02:54.980 --> 00:02:58.570 align:middle line:84%
in no shape to have any kind
of dream or hallucination.

00:02:58.570 --> 00:03:03.080 align:middle line:84%
My medical condition was such
that I went from having severe

00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:06.650 align:middle line:84%
headache and back pain in about
4:30 in the morning into grand

00:03:06.650 --> 00:03:10.117 align:middle line:84%
mal seizures and deep
coma within three hours.

00:03:10.117 --> 00:03:12.575 align:middle line:84%
And it was at that point that
my family was very concerned,

00:03:12.575 --> 00:03:15.660 align:middle line:84%
they called the
EMTs to come get me.

00:03:15.660 --> 00:03:17.010 align:middle line:90%
I remember none of that.

00:03:17.010 --> 00:03:19.370 align:middle line:84%
I was gone from this
world by that point,

00:03:19.370 --> 00:03:22.590 align:middle line:84%
taken to the emergency room
at Lynchburg General Hospital.

00:03:22.590 --> 00:03:25.350 align:middle line:84%
And I spent the next seven
days there deep in coma.

00:03:25.350 --> 00:03:27.680 align:middle line:84%
And the coma was
caused by meningitis.

00:03:27.680 --> 00:03:31.520 align:middle line:10%
And the neurologic exams,
my Glasgow Coma Scale,

00:03:31.520 --> 00:03:35.810 align:middle line:10%
my lab values, MR and
CT, every bit of that

00:03:35.810 --> 00:03:40.790 align:middle line:10%
showed that my brain was far too
incapacitated by this illness

00:03:40.790 --> 00:03:45.560 align:middle line:10%
and had no way of producing
any dream or hallucination.

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:48.680 align:middle line:84%
But for me, it was an
extraordinary journey

00:03:48.680 --> 00:03:49.530 align:middle line:90%
to go through.

00:03:49.530 --> 00:03:52.910 align:middle line:84%
In fact, for the first months
after awakening from coma,

00:03:52.910 --> 00:03:55.370 align:middle line:84%
it was a tremendous
challenge just trying

00:03:55.370 --> 00:03:57.600 align:middle line:84%
to explain how
this had happened.

00:03:57.600 --> 00:03:59.930 align:middle line:84%
But the more I discovered
about how ill I was,

00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:03.230 align:middle line:84%
the more I realized that this
was really impossible to explain

00:04:03.230 --> 00:04:06.980 align:middle line:84%
with our western medical
interpretation of things

00:04:06.980 --> 00:04:08.720 align:middle line:90%
and materialism.

00:04:08.720 --> 00:04:12.380 align:middle line:84%
And that is what shocked
me into realizing

00:04:12.380 --> 00:04:15.980 align:middle line:84%
that it seemed way too real
to be real because it really

00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:18.170 align:middle line:84%
happened, but not in
the physical world,

00:04:18.170 --> 00:04:21.380 align:middle line:84%
but in a much deeper, richer
place where I was interconnected

00:04:21.380 --> 00:04:23.480 align:middle line:84%
with all elements
of my soul journey,

00:04:23.480 --> 00:04:26.930 align:middle line:84%
including a birth sister who had
already left the physical plane.

00:04:26.930 --> 00:04:29.540 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of
mystery to this thing

00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:32.700 align:middle line:84%
we call brain-mind consciousness
and their relationship.

00:04:32.700 --> 00:04:34.490 align:middle line:84%
And I was just
beginning to discover

00:04:34.490 --> 00:04:37.220 align:middle line:90%
how profound that mystery was.

00:04:37.220 --> 00:04:38.730 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm Pim Van Lommel.

00:04:38.730 --> 00:04:41.090 align:middle line:84%
I'm a cardiologist
from the Netherlands.

00:04:41.090 --> 00:04:43.550 align:middle line:84%
I started to study
near-death experiences

00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:47.030 align:middle line:90%
many, many years ago in 1986.

00:04:47.030 --> 00:04:49.880 align:middle line:10%
I read a book by George
Ritchie, "Return from Tomorrow,"

00:04:49.880 --> 00:04:54.440 align:middle line:10%
where he describes where he died
as a medical student in 1943

00:04:54.440 --> 00:04:56.170 align:middle line:10%
because of double pneumonia.

00:04:56.170 --> 00:04:58.790 align:middle line:84%
But after nine minutes
of death, he came back,

00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:02.660 align:middle line:84%
and he had a very extensive
near-death experience.

00:05:02.660 --> 00:05:04.730 align:middle line:84%
So I was so impressed
by this book

00:05:04.730 --> 00:05:07.430 align:middle line:84%
that I started in '86
to ask a patient who

00:05:07.430 --> 00:05:10.075 align:middle line:84%
had survived the cardiac arrest
if he could remember something

00:05:10.075 --> 00:05:11.450 align:middle line:84%
from a period of
unconsciousness,

00:05:11.450 --> 00:05:13.130 align:middle line:84%
from the period
of cardiac arrest.

00:05:13.130 --> 00:05:15.800 align:middle line:84%
And to my big surprise,
within two years,

00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:18.620 align:middle line:84%
out of 50 patients who
survived cardiac arrest,

00:05:18.620 --> 00:05:21.320 align:middle line:84%
12 patients shared
their NDE with me.

00:05:21.320 --> 00:05:24.500 align:middle line:84%
And that started my
scientific curiosity,

00:05:24.500 --> 00:05:28.280 align:middle line:84%
because I've always learned it's
impossible to have experienced

00:05:28.280 --> 00:05:31.460 align:middle line:84%
consciousness, let alone
enhance consciousness

00:05:31.460 --> 00:05:33.650 align:middle line:84%
with the possibility of
perception out and above

00:05:33.650 --> 00:05:34.640 align:middle line:90%
your body.

00:05:34.640 --> 00:05:36.960 align:middle line:84%
With cognition, with
emotion, with memories,

00:05:36.960 --> 00:05:40.020 align:middle line:84%
with meeting deceased relatives,
it should be impossible.

00:05:40.020 --> 00:05:42.720 align:middle line:10%
So that's why we started
the study in 1988

00:05:42.720 --> 00:05:45.660 align:middle line:10%
to see if there could be
a scientific explanation

00:05:45.660 --> 00:05:48.420 align:middle line:10%
for the cause and
content of the NDE.

00:05:48.420 --> 00:05:51.135 align:middle line:84%
There was only one question
we had in our study,

00:05:51.135 --> 00:05:54.090 align:middle line:84%
and still use the
same question, do you

00:05:54.090 --> 00:05:56.220 align:middle line:84%
have memories from the
period of unconsciousness?

00:05:56.220 --> 00:05:58.512 align:middle line:84%
Do you have memories from
the period of cardiac arrest.

00:05:58.512 --> 00:06:01.000 align:middle line:90%
And they say no or they say why.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.840 align:middle line:84%
And when they say why, it
takes another hour because they

00:06:03.840 --> 00:06:06.880 align:middle line:90%
wanted to tell you.

00:06:06.880 --> 00:06:08.740 align:middle line:90%
And I know from all the stories.

00:06:08.740 --> 00:06:10.840 align:middle line:84%
I've met thousands
of people with NDE

00:06:10.840 --> 00:06:13.910 align:middle line:84%
and also tens of thousands of
emails from all over the world.

00:06:13.910 --> 00:06:16.390 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that
doctors don't listen.

00:06:16.390 --> 00:06:18.970 align:middle line:90%
Nurses are a little bit better.

00:06:18.970 --> 00:06:21.040 align:middle line:84%
Family members, friends
will not listen.

00:06:21.040 --> 00:06:23.630 align:middle line:84%
A partner is not able
to listen as well.

00:06:23.630 --> 00:06:26.380 align:middle line:84%
So there is a divorce
rate of more than 75%

00:06:26.380 --> 00:06:29.950 align:middle line:84%
because it's not the
person who married before.

00:06:29.950 --> 00:06:32.300 align:middle line:84%
And doctors say it's
just an hallucination.

00:06:32.300 --> 00:06:33.200 align:middle line:90%
It's a dream.

00:06:33.200 --> 00:06:34.580 align:middle line:90%
It's a side effect of drugs.

00:06:34.580 --> 00:06:36.040 align:middle line:90%
Here, you have some medication.

00:06:36.040 --> 00:06:37.240 align:middle line:90%
It will go over.

00:06:37.240 --> 00:06:38.600 align:middle line:90%
So they keep silent.

00:06:38.600 --> 00:06:41.230 align:middle line:84%
I have met people who have
been silent for 50 years

00:06:41.230 --> 00:06:43.890 align:middle line:84%
because they could
not share with others.

00:06:43.890 --> 00:06:48.610 align:middle line:84%
I know also from the church that
people have went to the minister

00:06:48.610 --> 00:06:52.010 align:middle line:84%
to share their story, and the
minister said, get out of here.

00:06:52.010 --> 00:06:53.920 align:middle line:90%
It was Satan.

00:06:53.920 --> 00:06:57.460 align:middle line:84%
>> I shared my experience with
close friends and with some

00:06:57.460 --> 00:07:01.210 align:middle line:84%
family, and it took me many
years to share it with, really,

00:07:01.210 --> 00:07:02.110 align:middle line:90%
all of them.

00:07:02.110 --> 00:07:05.440 align:middle line:84%
The hard part was, for the
first about four or five years,

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:08.780 align:middle line:84%
every time I would try to
talk about the experience,

00:07:08.780 --> 00:07:10.170 align:middle line:90%
I would just cry.

00:07:10.170 --> 00:07:13.710 align:middle line:84%
And it's because of that
love that I would feel there.

00:07:13.710 --> 00:07:16.130 align:middle line:84%
It's so hard to
even allow yourself

00:07:16.130 --> 00:07:20.010 align:middle line:84%
mentally to go there
without feeling all that.

00:07:20.010 --> 00:07:23.310 align:middle line:84%
And I knew not to meet any
more with the neurologists

00:07:23.310 --> 00:07:27.840 align:middle line:84%
because they kept trying to say
that everything was explainable

00:07:27.840 --> 00:07:29.790 align:middle line:84%
and that the
supplement that I took

00:07:29.790 --> 00:07:31.630 align:middle line:90%
was making my blood thinner.

00:07:31.630 --> 00:07:34.660 align:middle line:84%
That made it so that the
body didn't go fully dead,

00:07:34.660 --> 00:07:35.550 align:middle line:90%
but it was dead.

00:07:35.550 --> 00:07:36.358 align:middle line:90%
I know it was dead.

00:07:36.358 --> 00:07:37.900 align:middle line:84%
And I know because
I was watching it.

00:07:37.900 --> 00:07:40.305 align:middle line:90%
The body was fully dead.

00:07:40.305 --> 00:07:43.830 align:middle line:84%
And neurologists don't like
to talk about seeing your body

00:07:43.830 --> 00:07:45.480 align:middle line:90%
while you're above it.

00:07:45.480 --> 00:07:49.562 align:middle line:84%
I've never found one of them
that likes to talk about that.

00:07:49.562 --> 00:07:52.020 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think one problem
with the near-death experience

00:07:52.020 --> 00:07:54.750 align:middle line:84%
is it's so profound
and unexpected.

00:07:54.750 --> 00:07:58.050 align:middle line:84%
Certainly for me, as someone
like a materialist who

00:07:58.050 --> 00:08:01.500 align:middle line:84%
had gone through, wrestled
with these items through life,

00:08:01.500 --> 00:08:04.240 align:middle line:84%
thought, well, I just don't
see a way that it can happen.

00:08:04.240 --> 00:08:06.000 align:middle line:90%
And then going through it all.

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:08.680 align:middle line:84%
It's shocking, and
it's so ultra real,

00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:10.770 align:middle line:84%
it's such a different
mode of knowing

00:08:10.770 --> 00:08:13.020 align:middle line:84%
that often people come back
and think, well, if I try

00:08:13.020 --> 00:08:15.660 align:middle line:84%
and tell somebody that,
they'll think I'm crazy.

00:08:15.660 --> 00:08:18.990 align:middle line:84%
But when I first woke up, all I
knew was where I had just been,

00:08:18.990 --> 00:08:21.240 align:middle line:90%
this extraordinary journey.

00:08:21.240 --> 00:08:24.840 align:middle line:84%
So trying to make sense of it,
I would explain to my doctors

00:08:24.840 --> 00:08:28.890 align:middle line:84%
the spiritual fascination
of an incredible realm.

00:08:28.890 --> 00:08:30.510 align:middle line:84%
And they would just
pat me on the back

00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:32.860 align:middle line:84%
and say, well, your
brain was soaking in pus.

00:08:32.860 --> 00:08:35.220 align:middle line:84%
The dying brain plays
all kinds of tricks,

00:08:35.220 --> 00:08:38.210 align:middle line:90%
so you can just forget about it.

00:08:38.210 --> 00:08:41.870 align:middle line:84%
>> Nowadays there's a broad
familiarity with these

00:08:41.870 --> 00:08:45.750 align:middle line:84%
experiences, so people are more
comfortable talking about them.

00:08:45.750 --> 00:08:49.400 align:middle line:84%
But when I was doing this
research in the 1960s

00:08:49.400 --> 00:08:54.080 align:middle line:84%
and '70s, many of the people I
talked to had never told anybody

00:08:54.080 --> 00:08:56.040 align:middle line:90%
else except me about it.

00:08:56.040 --> 00:08:58.940 align:middle line:84%
They realized that nobody
was going to believe them,

00:08:58.940 --> 00:09:01.790 align:middle line:84%
that people would think
that they were mentally ill.

00:09:01.790 --> 00:09:04.040 align:middle line:84%
And a few of them
had actually tried

00:09:04.040 --> 00:09:06.740 align:middle line:84%
to tell their
physician who said,

00:09:06.740 --> 00:09:10.490 align:middle line:84%
oh, that was just a
hallucination, and dismiss it.

00:09:10.490 --> 00:09:14.630 align:middle line:84%
They had tried to tell their
minister who said, well,

00:09:14.630 --> 00:09:16.430 align:middle line:90%
that's out of my territory.

00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:19.910 align:middle line:84%
So there was nobody
for them to talk to.

00:09:19.910 --> 00:09:21.630 align:middle line:90%
>> It was very hard to process.

00:09:21.630 --> 00:09:23.070 align:middle line:90%
It's so hard to describe.

00:09:23.070 --> 00:09:25.190 align:middle line:84%
I would try to share it
with people at church,

00:09:25.190 --> 00:09:27.137 align:middle line:84%
and they were very
put off by it.

00:09:27.137 --> 00:09:29.720 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking, oh, I'll get
invited to all these churches

00:09:29.720 --> 00:09:30.550 align:middle line:90%
to speak.

00:09:30.550 --> 00:09:31.820 align:middle line:90%
Never happened.

00:09:31.820 --> 00:09:35.370 align:middle line:84%
And I'm trying to understand
this experience that I've had.

00:09:35.370 --> 00:09:37.960 align:middle line:84%
Everybody around me
thinks I'm crazy.

00:09:37.960 --> 00:09:40.470 align:middle line:84%
And it was really putting
a strain on my relationship

00:09:40.470 --> 00:09:42.840 align:middle line:90%
with myself and my husband.

00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:48.540 align:middle line:84%
>> It really takes a lot of guts
and love to give this story out

00:09:48.540 --> 00:09:52.600 align:middle line:84%
because some people can
question it, and that's fine.

00:09:52.600 --> 00:09:54.780 align:middle line:84%
I don't care if anybody
questions it or not.

00:09:54.780 --> 00:09:56.440 align:middle line:90%
I know it's the truth for me.

00:09:56.440 --> 00:09:59.160 align:middle line:84%
I know it's my life
that it happened in.

00:09:59.160 --> 00:10:03.450 align:middle line:84%
And I got so much education
from many other people who

00:10:03.450 --> 00:10:05.260 align:middle line:90%
had had near-death experiences.

00:10:05.260 --> 00:10:08.560 align:middle line:84%
It made me feel normal, like
other people are having them,

00:10:08.560 --> 00:10:10.200 align:middle line:90%
it's not just me.

00:10:10.200 --> 00:10:14.460 align:middle line:84%
>> There was a conference in the
US about near-death experiences.

00:10:14.460 --> 00:10:17.850 align:middle line:84%
So there was about 300 people
there have been lectures

00:10:17.850 --> 00:10:19.060 align:middle line:90%
about near-death experience.

00:10:19.060 --> 00:10:21.670 align:middle line:10%
And at the end, a man
stood up and said,

00:10:21.670 --> 00:10:24.340 align:middle line:10%
I'm a cardiologist for
more than 25 years,

00:10:24.340 --> 00:10:26.990 align:middle line:10%
I've never heard
such absurd stories.

00:10:26.990 --> 00:10:29.530 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe one word of it.

00:10:29.530 --> 00:10:32.740 align:middle line:84%
Then another man stood up
in the audience and said,

00:10:32.740 --> 00:10:34.330 align:middle line:90%
I'm one of your patients.

00:10:34.330 --> 00:10:36.890 align:middle line:84%
I've had a near-death
experience in cardiac arrest,

00:10:36.890 --> 00:10:39.970 align:middle line:84%
and you would be the last
one I would ever tell.

00:10:39.970 --> 00:10:41.920 align:middle line:84%
They know that these
kind of doctors

00:10:41.920 --> 00:10:44.650 align:middle line:90%
are not willing to listen.

00:10:44.650 --> 00:10:46.630 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the funny
things that happened was,

00:10:46.630 --> 00:10:52.660 align:middle line:84%
the first talk I gave on this to
a medical community was in '73.

00:10:52.660 --> 00:10:58.390 align:middle line:84%
And when I finished my talk, the
first person to hold up his hand

00:10:58.390 --> 00:11:00.380 align:middle line:90%
was one of my own professors.

00:11:00.380 --> 00:11:02.600 align:middle line:90%
He was an anatomy professor.

00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:04.020 align:middle line:84%
He said, this is
very interesting.

00:11:04.020 --> 00:11:04.820 align:middle line:90%
I'm interested.

00:11:04.820 --> 00:11:07.990 align:middle line:84%
He said, but I've been in
medicine a long time, why

00:11:07.990 --> 00:11:10.150 align:middle line:90%
haven't I ever heard of this?

00:11:10.150 --> 00:11:13.960 align:middle line:84%
So I just said, well, has
anybody here ever heard of this?

00:11:13.960 --> 00:11:19.870 align:middle line:84%
And this doctor's wife put up
her hand and she said, yes, yes.

00:11:19.870 --> 00:11:23.020 align:middle line:84%
And she said, don't you remember
our friend Helen came over

00:11:23.020 --> 00:11:25.000 align:middle line:90%
and she was talking about this?

00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:28.450 align:middle line:90%
And so it's that people--

00:11:28.450 --> 00:11:32.320 align:middle line:84%
some people, this is just too
much and they won't hear it.

00:11:32.320 --> 00:11:37.130 align:middle line:84%
So it's not a matter of
volume of numbers of cases.

00:11:37.130 --> 00:11:40.780 align:middle line:84%
The real difficulty is
the conceptual apparatus

00:11:40.780 --> 00:11:43.420 align:middle line:90%
for how we think about this.

00:11:43.420 --> 00:11:47.450 align:middle line:84%
>> So a near-death experience
is the reported memory of a lot

00:11:47.450 --> 00:11:50.340 align:middle line:84%
of impressions during a
special state of consciousness.

00:11:50.340 --> 00:11:52.550 align:middle line:84%
And this special
state of consciousness

00:11:52.550 --> 00:11:54.950 align:middle line:84%
can happen during a
critical medical situation,

00:11:54.950 --> 00:11:56.160 align:middle line:90%
like cardiac arrest.

00:11:56.160 --> 00:11:57.620 align:middle line:90%
You can have it in a coma.

00:11:57.620 --> 00:12:01.010 align:middle line:84%
But until we started
our prospective study,

00:12:01.010 --> 00:12:03.770 align:middle line:84%
the main explanation
was lack of oxygen

00:12:03.770 --> 00:12:08.750 align:middle line:84%
in your brain, A hallucination,
dreams, just fancy tales trying

00:12:08.750 --> 00:12:11.690 align:middle line:84%
to be interesting, et cetera,
a side effect of drugs.

00:12:11.690 --> 00:12:15.850 align:middle line:84%
But it had never been proven, so
we needed to prospective study

00:12:15.850 --> 00:12:18.050 align:middle line:84%
to see if we could
find an explanation

00:12:18.050 --> 00:12:20.210 align:middle line:84%
for the causal
content of an NDE.

00:12:20.210 --> 00:12:23.360 align:middle line:10%
And what we found is 18%
of those patients who

00:12:23.360 --> 00:12:25.130 align:middle line:10%
survived a cardiac
arrest told us

00:12:25.130 --> 00:12:26.850 align:middle line:10%
about their
near-death experience.

00:12:26.850 --> 00:12:30.480 align:middle line:84%
And 82% did not have
any memory at all.

00:12:30.480 --> 00:12:33.230 align:middle line:84%
And we compared the two
groups of patients, the group

00:12:33.230 --> 00:12:35.000 align:middle line:90%
with and without an NDE.

00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:37.220 align:middle line:84%
There was no, to our
surprise, difference

00:12:37.220 --> 00:12:39.092 align:middle line:84%
at all in the duration
of cardiac arrest.

00:12:39.092 --> 00:12:40.550 align:middle line:84%
It was two minutes
or eight minutes

00:12:40.550 --> 00:12:42.240 align:middle line:84%
or the duration of
unconsciousness.

00:12:42.240 --> 00:12:44.390 align:middle line:84%
If it was five minutes
or three weeks of coma,

00:12:44.390 --> 00:12:47.560 align:middle line:84%
the severity of the lack
of oxygen in the brain

00:12:47.560 --> 00:12:48.890 align:middle line:90%
did not matter at all.

00:12:48.890 --> 00:12:50.860 align:middle line:84%
We could exclude
the lack of oxygen

00:12:50.860 --> 00:12:52.790 align:middle line:84%
in the brain because
of our study.

00:12:52.790 --> 00:12:55.660 align:middle line:84%
And also, we could exclude
side effects of drugs.

00:12:55.660 --> 00:12:57.410 align:middle line:84%
There was no difference
in the medication.

00:12:57.410 --> 00:12:58.960 align:middle line:90%
People had with and without.

00:12:58.960 --> 00:13:01.270 align:middle line:84%
Fear of death, the
psychological explanation,

00:13:01.270 --> 00:13:02.660 align:middle line:90%
did not matter at all.

00:13:02.660 --> 00:13:05.548 align:middle line:90%
Education, gender, religion.

00:13:05.548 --> 00:13:07.465 align:middle line:84%
If they were Christian,
or atheist, or Muslim,

00:13:07.465 --> 00:13:08.890 align:middle line:90%
it didn't matter at all.

00:13:08.890 --> 00:13:13.030 align:middle line:84%
So there was no scientific
explanation at all

00:13:13.030 --> 00:13:18.100 align:middle line:84%
to explain why people have
an NDE during cardiac arrest.

00:13:18.100 --> 00:13:20.900 align:middle line:84%
>> And one thing when you
actually study delusion,

00:13:20.900 --> 00:13:24.050 align:middle line:84%
so I actually did do a
little research on my own,

00:13:24.050 --> 00:13:27.560 align:middle line:84%
oxygen to the brain is still
required to have a delusion.

00:13:27.560 --> 00:13:31.540 align:middle line:10%
So to be no oxygen to
the brain as long as I

00:13:31.540 --> 00:13:35.080 align:middle line:10%
was, at least an
hour, possibly two,

00:13:35.080 --> 00:13:38.470 align:middle line:10%
according to different people
how they rate how much time I

00:13:38.470 --> 00:13:41.080 align:middle line:10%
was actually dead, it
was impossible to be

00:13:41.080 --> 00:13:43.610 align:middle line:10%
having any delusion.

00:13:43.610 --> 00:13:46.040 align:middle line:84%
>> There's all this talk
of people trying to give

00:13:46.040 --> 00:13:49.370 align:middle line:84%
a physiological or a clinical
explanation for a near-death

00:13:49.370 --> 00:13:50.340 align:middle line:90%
experience.

00:13:50.340 --> 00:13:52.190 align:middle line:84%
So commonly, those
arguments are, well,

00:13:52.190 --> 00:13:54.800 align:middle line:84%
the brain was deprived
of oxygen and there's

00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:57.200 align:middle line:84%
chemicals being shot around
in the brain that will cause

00:13:57.200 --> 00:13:58.930 align:middle line:90%
these hallucinatory events.

00:13:58.930 --> 00:14:00.330 align:middle line:90%
That was not the case for me.

00:14:00.330 --> 00:14:01.910 align:middle line:84%
I was in a coma,
my oxygen levels

00:14:01.910 --> 00:14:03.750 align:middle line:84%
were being controlled
by a ventilator.

00:14:03.750 --> 00:14:07.040 align:middle line:84%
Then they'll say, oh, it's the
drugs, those drugs that they use

00:14:07.040 --> 00:14:09.440 align:middle line:84%
to induce coma or
induce deep sleep

00:14:09.440 --> 00:14:12.840 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, those are
causing hallucinations.

00:14:12.840 --> 00:14:16.680 align:middle line:84%
But the nature of hallucinations
is that they're very confusing.

00:14:16.680 --> 00:14:18.960 align:middle line:84%
They're jumbled, and they
don't seem to make sense,

00:14:18.960 --> 00:14:20.130 align:middle line:90%
they're not cohesive.

00:14:20.130 --> 00:14:22.410 align:middle line:84%
The memory of them
fades with time.

00:14:22.410 --> 00:14:24.690 align:middle line:84%
You don't see that with
near-death experiences.

00:14:24.690 --> 00:14:28.460 align:middle line:84%
When those people come back
and describe their experiences,

00:14:28.460 --> 00:14:32.480 align:middle line:84%
they're very lucid, they're
ordered, they're chronological,

00:14:32.480 --> 00:14:35.570 align:middle line:84%
and they tend to open up
more the longer that you

00:14:35.570 --> 00:14:37.340 align:middle line:90%
process them.

00:14:37.340 --> 00:14:41.240 align:middle line:84%
>> There are many different
mechanisms that materialist

00:14:41.240 --> 00:14:44.750 align:middle line:84%
scientists come up with to try
and explain away near-death

00:14:44.750 --> 00:14:45.550 align:middle line:90%
experiences.

00:14:45.550 --> 00:14:47.342 align:middle line:84%
They're trying to
pretend that they're just

00:14:47.342 --> 00:14:51.190 align:middle line:84%
hallucinations or some chaotic
action of the dying brain.

00:14:51.190 --> 00:14:54.210 align:middle line:84%
But what they're missing
is, for one thing,

00:14:54.210 --> 00:14:57.780 align:middle line:84%
the similarity of near-death
experiences across all kinds

00:14:57.780 --> 00:14:59.260 align:middle line:90%
of disease states.

00:14:59.260 --> 00:15:02.220 align:middle line:84%
If all these different brain
mechanisms were active,

00:15:02.220 --> 00:15:06.250 align:middle line:84%
why wouldn't we see a lot of
very different experiences.

00:15:06.250 --> 00:15:08.940 align:middle line:84%
And yet, the experiences
have tremendous commonalities

00:15:08.940 --> 00:15:10.110 align:middle line:90%
between them.

00:15:10.110 --> 00:15:12.360 align:middle line:84%
For example, it's
not at all uncommon

00:15:12.360 --> 00:15:16.410 align:middle line:84%
for near-death experiencers
whose mental awareness has been

00:15:16.410 --> 00:15:21.630 align:middle line:84%
liberated to that level to
be aware of ongoing actions

00:15:21.630 --> 00:15:23.830 align:middle line:84%
in the here and now,
in the physical world.

00:15:23.830 --> 00:15:26.520 align:middle line:84%
For example, in Anita
Moorjani's case,

00:15:26.520 --> 00:15:28.500 align:middle line:84%
as she was deep in
the spiritual realm,

00:15:28.500 --> 00:15:31.200 align:middle line:84%
she was fully in touch
with her brother.

00:15:31.200 --> 00:15:35.130 align:middle line:84%
He was on a plane flying
from India to Hong Kong,

00:15:35.130 --> 00:15:36.700 align:middle line:90%
possibly for her funeral.

00:15:36.700 --> 00:15:38.310 align:middle line:84%
And yet, she could
connect with him

00:15:38.310 --> 00:15:42.150 align:middle line:84%
and know exactly what was going
on in his mind at a distance.

00:15:42.150 --> 00:15:45.480 align:middle line:84%
But simultaneously,
she was able to connect

00:15:45.480 --> 00:15:48.330 align:middle line:84%
with the soul of her
father, who had passed over

00:15:48.330 --> 00:15:50.820 align:middle line:90%
and had very profound lessons.

00:15:50.820 --> 00:15:53.580 align:middle line:84%
>> We hear all these cases,
and I've seen them myself,

00:15:53.580 --> 00:15:57.660 align:middle line:84%
where the person, while
they were out of their body,

00:15:57.660 --> 00:16:00.900 align:middle line:84%
seems to be able to see
something in the room

00:16:00.900 --> 00:16:04.080 align:middle line:84%
or the scene of the
resuscitation where it is

00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:06.210 align:middle line:90%
subsequently confirmed.

00:16:06.210 --> 00:16:09.150 align:middle line:84%
And that is a very puzzling
and interesting thing,

00:16:09.150 --> 00:16:10.980 align:middle line:90%
and I hear it all the time.

00:16:10.980 --> 00:16:14.670 align:middle line:84%
But then you get into a
question not of medicine,

00:16:14.670 --> 00:16:17.040 align:middle line:90%
but of epistemology.

00:16:17.040 --> 00:16:22.600 align:middle line:84%
The question then is, can we
know that these things are real?

00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:26.170 align:middle line:84%
And I've always been
impressed by the fact

00:16:26.170 --> 00:16:29.200 align:middle line:84%
that people who have
these experiences, they

00:16:29.200 --> 00:16:32.860 align:middle line:84%
all unanimously assure
me that not only was

00:16:32.860 --> 00:16:36.940 align:middle line:84%
their experience real, but
that it was more real than what

00:16:36.940 --> 00:16:39.400 align:middle line:90%
we're going through now.

00:16:39.400 --> 00:16:41.500 align:middle line:84%
>> When you have a
near-death experience,

00:16:41.500 --> 00:16:47.350 align:middle line:84%
it is more real than the current
environment that you're in.

00:16:47.350 --> 00:16:50.800 align:middle line:84%
So I didn't question it
at all as a hallucination

00:16:50.800 --> 00:16:53.110 align:middle line:90%
or a dream, no.

00:16:53.110 --> 00:16:55.990 align:middle line:84%
I was out of my body
watching what they were doing

00:16:55.990 --> 00:16:58.670 align:middle line:90%
down below to resuscitate me.

00:16:58.670 --> 00:17:00.680 align:middle line:90%
I heard them calling code blue.

00:17:00.680 --> 00:17:02.510 align:middle line:90%
I saw the flatline.

00:17:02.510 --> 00:17:04.040 align:middle line:90%
I knew that I was dead.

00:17:04.040 --> 00:17:07.150 align:middle line:84%
I knew that I was up above
my body on the ceiling.

00:17:07.150 --> 00:17:10.000 align:middle line:84%
And there was no question
about that at all.

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:13.720 align:middle line:84%
>> It's so vivid, this
kind of memory of the NDE.

00:17:13.720 --> 00:17:16.480 align:middle line:84%
And they say, being
back in the body,

00:17:16.480 --> 00:17:20.060 align:middle line:84%
this physical world around
me is like an illusion.

00:17:20.060 --> 00:17:22.579 align:middle line:84%
But what happened to
me in my consciousness,

00:17:22.579 --> 00:17:26.030 align:middle line:84%
in the higher dimension,
that's more real than real.

00:17:26.030 --> 00:17:28.730 align:middle line:90%
They just feel home.

00:17:28.730 --> 00:17:30.820 align:middle line:90%
They don't believe anymore.

00:17:30.820 --> 00:17:32.170 align:middle line:90%
They know.

00:17:32.170 --> 00:17:35.320 align:middle line:90%
They've been there.

00:17:35.320 --> 00:17:37.690 align:middle line:84%
>> I would say that is one
of the most astonishing

00:17:37.690 --> 00:17:39.770 align:middle line:84%
characteristics of
these experiences.

00:17:39.770 --> 00:17:42.760 align:middle line:84%
People often assume that
they'll be vague, and murky,

00:17:42.760 --> 00:17:44.740 align:middle line:84%
and dream like,
well, I'll tell you

00:17:44.740 --> 00:17:47.950 align:middle line:84%
that having been there, this
world, this material world

00:17:47.950 --> 00:17:50.330 align:middle line:84%
is vague, and murky,
and dreamlike.

00:17:50.330 --> 00:17:52.660 align:middle line:84%
That world of the
spiritual realm

00:17:52.660 --> 00:17:56.000 align:middle line:84%
is sharp, clear,
crisp, transformative.

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:58.940 align:middle line:84%
You remember those
events for decades,

00:17:58.940 --> 00:18:00.800 align:middle line:90%
they do not fade from memory.

00:18:00.800 --> 00:18:03.490 align:middle line:84%
It's really astonishing
how powerful

00:18:03.490 --> 00:18:06.370 align:middle line:84%
the ultra reality
of that realm is.

00:18:06.370 --> 00:18:09.310 align:middle line:84%
That's what makes these
stories ineffable, so difficult

00:18:09.310 --> 00:18:12.370 align:middle line:84%
to describe, because from
that eternal perspective,

00:18:12.370 --> 00:18:14.800 align:middle line:84%
you can see the connections
so much more readily

00:18:14.800 --> 00:18:18.510 align:middle line:84%
and everything makes
far more sense.

00:18:18.510 --> 00:18:22.650 align:middle line:84%
>> I've talked with people who
were not religious and who were

00:18:22.650 --> 00:18:23.550 align:middle line:90%
religious.

00:18:23.550 --> 00:18:27.900 align:middle line:84%
And what I've realized is
that it really doesn't matter.

00:18:27.900 --> 00:18:31.020 align:middle line:84%
The language itself
fails no matter

00:18:31.020 --> 00:18:33.750 align:middle line:84%
what your religion
was, that there

00:18:33.750 --> 00:18:38.250 align:middle line:84%
isn't any conceptual scheme
that is satisfactory to try

00:18:38.250 --> 00:18:40.560 align:middle line:90%
to make sense of this.

00:18:40.560 --> 00:18:44.190 align:middle line:84%
>> My experience there
was more real than here.

00:18:44.190 --> 00:18:46.510 align:middle line:84%
Again, it's hard to
explain with words,

00:18:46.510 --> 00:18:49.380 align:middle line:84%
but truly, there is
the real existence.

00:18:49.380 --> 00:18:52.890 align:middle line:84%
There is the real colors you
see, the real energy you see,

00:18:52.890 --> 00:18:55.600 align:middle line:84%
and you just know things
that you shouldn't know.

00:18:55.600 --> 00:18:58.770 align:middle line:84%
And some of that has had
a lingering effect on me.

00:18:58.770 --> 00:19:00.570 align:middle line:84%
There's been many
times in my life

00:19:00.570 --> 00:19:03.090 align:middle line:84%
where I go into a
deep state of hypnosis

00:19:03.090 --> 00:19:07.890 align:middle line:84%
or a deep state of
meditation, and I can actually

00:19:07.890 --> 00:19:11.580 align:middle line:90%
get myself there again.

00:19:11.580 --> 00:19:13.660 align:middle line:90%
>> It's always vivid.

00:19:13.660 --> 00:19:16.410 align:middle line:84%
They still keep it alive
even though it might

00:19:16.410 --> 00:19:18.960 align:middle line:90%
have happened decades before.

00:19:18.960 --> 00:19:22.020 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't mean, by the
way, that these things

00:19:22.020 --> 00:19:23.860 align:middle line:90%
are easy to figure out.

00:19:23.860 --> 00:19:27.610 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is really a
very difficult question.

00:19:27.610 --> 00:19:33.150 align:middle line:84%
Maybe we need some new way to
investigate this kind of thing.

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:37.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Most materialist-based
scientists have to believe

00:19:37.470 --> 00:19:41.100 align:middle line:84%
in a never proven assumption,
that the brain produces

00:19:41.100 --> 00:19:42.100 align:middle line:90%
consciousness.

00:19:42.100 --> 00:19:45.030 align:middle line:84%
It's their dogma, it's
their belief system.

00:19:45.030 --> 00:19:48.480 align:middle line:84%
But based on scientific
research in patients

00:19:48.480 --> 00:19:51.840 align:middle line:84%
who survived cardiac arrest,
when the brain doesn't function

00:19:51.840 --> 00:19:54.330 align:middle line:84%
at all, you have the
possibility of perception

00:19:54.330 --> 00:19:55.980 align:middle line:90%
out and above your body.

00:19:55.980 --> 00:20:00.420 align:middle line:84%
Blind people can perceive, deaf
people know what has been said.

00:20:00.420 --> 00:20:03.540 align:middle line:84%
And you can ask the doctors, and
nurses, and family members what

00:20:03.540 --> 00:20:05.310 align:middle line:90%
really happened at what time.

00:20:05.310 --> 00:20:10.140 align:middle line:84%
So that means this corroboration
proves that without a brain

00:20:10.140 --> 00:20:12.220 align:middle line:90%
function, you have perception.

00:20:12.220 --> 00:20:13.560 align:middle line:10%
That's impossible.

00:20:13.560 --> 00:20:15.640 align:middle line:10%
It should be impossible,
but it happens.

00:20:15.640 --> 00:20:18.100 align:middle line:84%
So you can ignore
the new findings

00:20:18.100 --> 00:20:20.950 align:middle line:90%
or you can change the paradigm.

00:20:20.950 --> 00:20:23.980 align:middle line:84%
>> The traditional model is
really one of brain creates

00:20:23.980 --> 00:20:27.590 align:middle line:84%
consciousness, that is what we
can see happening in the brain,

00:20:27.590 --> 00:20:30.250 align:middle line:84%
like with functional MRI,
magnetoencephalography,

00:20:30.250 --> 00:20:33.880 align:middle line:84%
those kind of techniques, they
should correlate with things

00:20:33.880 --> 00:20:36.560 align:middle line:84%
that occur in phenomenal
consciousness.

00:20:36.560 --> 00:20:38.350 align:middle line:84%
And the general
idea in materialists

00:20:38.350 --> 00:20:41.290 align:middle line:84%
is that the material
itself of the brain

00:20:41.290 --> 00:20:43.380 align:middle line:90%
is causing all of that.

00:20:43.380 --> 00:20:45.250 align:middle line:84%
And because the
material in the brain

00:20:45.250 --> 00:20:48.850 align:middle line:84%
is subject to the laws of
physics, chemistry, and biology,

00:20:48.850 --> 00:20:50.740 align:middle line:84%
when you pay attention
to that argument, what

00:20:50.740 --> 00:20:53.080 align:middle line:84%
they're telling you is
you do not have free will.

00:20:53.080 --> 00:20:54.610 align:middle line:84%
They're saying
that consciousness

00:20:54.610 --> 00:20:57.610 align:middle line:84%
