And I'm not perfect,
but I do want

00:30:59.360 --> 00:31:02.780 align:middle line:10%
to try to help people, and
give what I can to others,

00:31:02.780 --> 00:31:08.120 align:middle line:10%
and spend my time in a valuable
way of just even just talking

00:31:08.120 --> 00:31:10.610 align:middle line:10%
to someone who needs
a listening ear.

00:31:10.610 --> 00:31:13.010 align:middle line:84%
And up on the
ceiling, I was shown

00:31:13.010 --> 00:31:16.500 align:middle line:84%
that there was other work that I
was supposed to do with my life,

00:31:16.500 --> 00:31:19.650 align:middle line:84%
there was purpose that
I needed to complete.

00:31:19.650 --> 00:31:24.720 align:middle line:84%
So I think I'm doing that
with what I do in my life now.

00:31:24.720 --> 00:31:26.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Then you changed
the way you live.

00:31:26.420 --> 00:31:30.990 align:middle line:84%
So it's not anymore
about money, about power,

00:31:30.990 --> 00:31:35.880 align:middle line:84%
and there's no death anymore,
they believe in an afterlife.

00:31:35.880 --> 00:31:37.740 align:middle line:84%
It's a continuity
of consciousness

00:31:37.740 --> 00:31:40.130 align:middle line:90%
after the death of the body.

00:31:40.130 --> 00:31:44.330 align:middle line:84%
So death is like birth, a
changing state of consciousness,

00:31:44.330 --> 00:31:48.140 align:middle line:90%
that there will never be an end.

00:31:48.140 --> 00:31:51.020 align:middle line:84%
>> The first time I had
someone close to me die after

00:31:51.020 --> 00:31:53.850 align:middle line:90%
my experience, it was weird.

00:31:53.850 --> 00:31:55.730 align:middle line:90%
There was this dual suffering.

00:31:55.730 --> 00:31:59.300 align:middle line:84%
I was suffering that I
was losing a loved one,

00:31:59.300 --> 00:32:01.590 align:middle line:84%
but at the same
time, I was jealous.

00:32:01.590 --> 00:32:06.590 align:middle line:84%
I had this jealousy that, why
did they get to go before me?

00:32:06.590 --> 00:32:09.900 align:middle line:84%
It's weird to say, but once
you're there, you understand it.

00:32:09.900 --> 00:32:12.680 align:middle line:84%
You understand that you're
excited when your day comes,

00:32:12.680 --> 00:32:16.170 align:middle line:84%
you don't hide from it,
you're not worried about it.

00:32:16.170 --> 00:32:19.320 align:middle line:84%
Whereas a lot of other
people, they're freaking out.

00:32:19.320 --> 00:32:21.650 align:middle line:84%
But if they really knew what
was there to greet them,

00:32:21.650 --> 00:32:23.490 align:middle line:84%
they wouldn't be
freaking out ever.

00:32:23.490 --> 00:32:27.980 align:middle line:84%
Because I've already been
where this life is past

00:32:27.980 --> 00:32:31.100 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not actively
trying to bring that on,

00:32:31.100 --> 00:32:34.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm respecting God's plan
and the creator's plan,

00:32:34.160 --> 00:32:37.160 align:middle line:84%
but at the same time, I'm
not afraid of it at all.

00:32:37.160 --> 00:32:38.820 align:middle line:90%
>> So many people fear that.

00:32:38.820 --> 00:32:41.750 align:middle line:84%
They fear their infirmity
and their death.

00:32:41.750 --> 00:32:43.830 align:middle line:84%
And I don't fear
any of those things.

00:32:43.830 --> 00:32:45.620 align:middle line:84%
I know they're
coming for all of us,

00:32:45.620 --> 00:32:47.690 align:middle line:84%
and I know what's
on the other side,

00:32:47.690 --> 00:32:49.730 align:middle line:90%
and I'm ready to go whenever.

00:32:49.730 --> 00:32:53.630 align:middle line:84%
But I've lost my cousin
who was beloved to me

00:32:53.630 --> 00:32:55.620 align:middle line:90%
since my near-death experience.

00:32:55.620 --> 00:32:57.078 align:middle line:84%
And I remember when
I got the news,

00:32:57.078 --> 00:32:59.203 align:middle line:84%
I took it just like anybody
else who would not have

00:32:59.203 --> 00:33:00.390 align:middle line:90%
had a near-death experience.

00:33:00.390 --> 00:33:03.390 align:middle line:84%
I remember the room shifted
and I almost fell down.

00:33:03.390 --> 00:33:05.330 align:middle line:84%
And I was crying,
and I was thinking,

00:33:05.330 --> 00:33:07.090 align:middle line:90%
who is crying so loudly?

00:33:07.090 --> 00:33:09.370 align:middle line:90%
And it was surreal.

00:33:09.370 --> 00:33:14.170 align:middle line:84%
So it's still hard, but
it's not as hard as it was.

00:33:14.170 --> 00:33:18.310 align:middle line:84%
And death is very
neglected in our culture.

00:33:18.310 --> 00:33:20.330 align:middle line:84%
It's something that
everybody's scared of,

00:33:20.330 --> 00:33:22.210 align:middle line:90%
they're scared to talk about it.

00:33:22.210 --> 00:33:26.290 align:middle line:84%
>> It has been known in all
religions, and all cultures,

00:33:26.290 --> 00:33:29.350 align:middle line:84%
and all times that
death is not the end.

00:33:29.350 --> 00:33:33.550 align:middle line:84%
But we have lost this knowledge
in the last 300 years.

00:33:33.550 --> 00:33:36.760 align:middle line:84%
So death is for a lot
of people still a taboo.

00:33:36.760 --> 00:33:38.500 align:middle line:90%
People have fear.

00:33:38.500 --> 00:33:42.520 align:middle line:84%
They believe that death is
the end of everything we are.

00:33:42.520 --> 00:33:45.370 align:middle line:84%
That was my idea as well when I
was a young doctor, I thought,

00:33:45.370 --> 00:33:47.210 align:middle line:84%
death is the end of
everything we are.

00:33:47.210 --> 00:33:49.450 align:middle line:84%
But I've changed my
ideas because I've

00:33:49.450 --> 00:33:51.990 align:middle line:90%
met so many people with NDE.

00:33:51.990 --> 00:33:56.100 align:middle line:84%
I always tell people that people
with NDE have been my teachers,

00:33:56.100 --> 00:33:59.910 align:middle line:84%
they have learned me that
death is not the end.

00:33:59.910 --> 00:34:03.007 align:middle line:84%
>> And so if you know
going in that any day--

00:34:03.007 --> 00:34:04.590 align:middle line:84%
my parents are getting
older, any day,

00:34:04.590 --> 00:34:07.390 align:middle line:84%
I could get a call that
I've lost one of my parents.

00:34:07.390 --> 00:34:09.190 align:middle line:84%
I know that that is
eventually coming.

00:34:09.190 --> 00:34:11.110 align:middle line:90%
We all have an expiration date.

00:34:11.110 --> 00:34:13.739 align:middle line:84%
And so when it comes,
because I know that

00:34:13.739 --> 00:34:17.610 align:middle line:84%
and I'm facing that reality,
yes, it's going to be difficult,

00:34:17.610 --> 00:34:20.340 align:middle line:84%
but I'm not going to be
totally knocked flat by it.

00:34:20.340 --> 00:34:22.469 align:middle line:84%
And we'll get through
it and we'll somehow

00:34:22.469 --> 00:34:24.929 align:middle line:90%
be better on the other side.

00:34:24.929 --> 00:34:29.310 align:middle line:84%
>> The goal is, for all of us,
that as those who do around us

00:34:29.310 --> 00:34:33.330 align:middle line:84%
pass, as they cross over,
that we love them through it,

00:34:33.330 --> 00:34:35.650 align:middle line:84%
that we love them
into their transition.

00:34:35.650 --> 00:34:39.250 align:middle line:84%
And as we love them, it makes
their transition even easier.

00:34:39.250 --> 00:34:43.389 align:middle line:84%
And if we can, if we believe
in this, pray for them.

00:34:43.389 --> 00:34:45.630 align:middle line:84%
It's going to help them
through their transition

00:34:45.630 --> 00:34:49.080 align:middle line:84%
and it's going to help us
being OK that they transitioned

00:34:49.080 --> 00:34:50.550 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:34:50.550 --> 00:34:54.420 align:middle line:84%
>> So when I do lose someone,
one of all three of the elderly

00:34:54.420 --> 00:34:57.240 align:middle line:84%
people that passed
on in my life, yes,

00:34:57.240 --> 00:35:00.700 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to miss them terribly
with the interactions that we

00:35:00.700 --> 00:35:04.130 align:middle line:84%
had and the relationship
we had developed,

00:35:04.130 --> 00:35:08.030 align:middle line:84%
but I know that they're fine
up there on the other side.

00:35:08.030 --> 00:35:11.950 align:middle line:84%
I know that at home,
they are perfectly well.

00:35:11.950 --> 00:35:15.010 align:middle line:84%
>> People who come back from a
near-death experience say they

00:35:15.010 --> 00:35:17.180 align:middle line:90%
have no more fear of death.

00:35:17.180 --> 00:35:20.720 align:middle line:84%
And that has rubbed
off on me for sure.

00:35:20.720 --> 00:35:22.670 align:middle line:90%
I am not afraid of death.

00:35:22.670 --> 00:35:25.480 align:middle line:84%
Pain is something
I'm afraid of, but I

00:35:25.480 --> 00:35:32.050 align:middle line:84%
have this confidence that, well,
this is not everything there is.

00:35:32.050 --> 00:35:36.340 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time, it
focuses your attention

00:35:36.340 --> 00:35:39.850 align:middle line:84%
on what it means to
be alive now, what

00:35:39.850 --> 00:35:41.533 align:middle line:90%
is it about us that survives?

00:35:41.533 --> 00:35:44.070 align:middle line:90%


00:35:44.070 --> 00:35:47.020 align:middle line:84%
>> And the real beauty of the
journey is demonstrated to those

00:35:47.020 --> 00:35:48.520 align:middle line:84%
who have had
near-death experiences.

00:35:48.520 --> 00:35:52.010 align:middle line:84%
And they will tell you, there
is nothing to fear about death.

00:35:52.010 --> 00:35:55.800 align:middle line:84%
Death is a natural transition,
it's part of the soul journey.

00:35:55.800 --> 00:35:58.320 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, our souls
come back again and again

00:35:58.320 --> 00:36:02.400 align:middle line:84%
in this process of reaching
towards oneness with the divine

00:36:02.400 --> 00:36:06.210 align:middle line:84%
in that state of enlightenment,
which is what all of us

00:36:06.210 --> 00:36:09.160 align:middle line:90%
are headed for ultimately.

00:36:09.160 --> 00:36:12.580 align:middle line:10%
>> And about the fear of death,
perhaps we didn't talk about it,

00:36:12.580 --> 00:36:14.650 align:middle line:10%
is after death communication.

00:36:14.650 --> 00:36:19.690 align:middle line:84%
So in the first days or weeks
after the death of a loved one,

00:36:19.690 --> 00:36:21.880 align:middle line:84%
there's a huge
possibility that you

00:36:21.880 --> 00:36:23.620 align:middle line:84%
will be in contact
with the consciousness

00:36:23.620 --> 00:36:27.500 align:middle line:84%
of deceased relative, usually to
tell them, I'm all right here.

00:36:27.500 --> 00:36:28.330 align:middle line:90%
Don't worry.

00:36:28.330 --> 00:36:29.920 align:middle line:90%
It's fine with me.

00:36:29.920 --> 00:36:33.550 align:middle line:84%
About 125 million
people in Europe

00:36:33.550 --> 00:36:35.290 align:middle line:84%
have this after
death communication,

00:36:35.290 --> 00:36:38.210 align:middle line:84%
usually during sleep, because
the threshold of consciousness

00:36:38.210 --> 00:36:39.010 align:middle line:90%
is lower.

00:36:39.010 --> 00:36:42.040 align:middle line:10%
So people who have died
have more possibility

00:36:42.040 --> 00:36:45.010 align:middle line:10%
to have access to the
consciousness of the people

00:36:45.010 --> 00:36:46.780 align:middle line:10%
up here on Earth.

00:36:46.780 --> 00:36:49.780 align:middle line:10%
And they call it a
dream, but usually, you

00:36:49.780 --> 00:36:50.870 align:middle line:10%
don't remember a dream.

00:36:50.870 --> 00:36:54.740 align:middle line:84%
But this is such a-- we call
it a conscious experience

00:36:54.740 --> 00:36:57.020 align:middle line:84%
during sleep, you
will never forget it.

00:36:57.020 --> 00:37:00.550 align:middle line:10%
The contact with the one
who died is so impressive,

00:37:00.550 --> 00:37:02.350 align:middle line:10%
sometimes you get
information it's

00:37:02.350 --> 00:37:05.290 align:middle line:10%
impossible to know beforehand.

00:37:05.290 --> 00:37:08.020 align:middle line:10%
And it happened so often,
but they don't talk about it

00:37:08.020 --> 00:37:10.190 align:middle line:10%
because when you try
to talk about it,

00:37:10.190 --> 00:37:12.630 align:middle line:10%
it's all just a dream,
it's just your morning,

00:37:12.630 --> 00:37:14.450 align:middle line:10%
don't believe it, et cetera.

00:37:14.450 --> 00:37:16.970 align:middle line:84%
And that's the same as the
perimortem experience, where

00:37:16.970 --> 00:37:20.280 align:middle line:84%
you are asleep and you
get awake at 4 o'clock.

00:37:20.280 --> 00:37:21.410 align:middle line:90%
You think of your father.

00:37:21.410 --> 00:37:22.830 align:middle line:90%
You get sad, et cetera.

00:37:22.830 --> 00:37:24.410 align:middle line:84%
And then the next
morning, you get

00:37:24.410 --> 00:37:27.532 align:middle line:84%
a phone call that your father
died at that very moment.

00:37:27.532 --> 00:37:29.240 align:middle line:84%
There are so many,
many things happening,

00:37:29.240 --> 00:37:32.240 align:middle line:84%
but people are so
reluctant to share it.

00:37:32.240 --> 00:37:33.740 align:middle line:84%
And the same kind
of experience can

00:37:33.740 --> 00:37:35.750 align:middle line:84%
happen in the terminal
phase of illness,

00:37:35.750 --> 00:37:39.380 align:middle line:84%
what we call the end of
life experiences as well.

00:37:39.380 --> 00:37:43.010 align:middle line:84%
>> I had a lot of patients that
were at the end of their life,

00:37:43.010 --> 00:37:47.360 align:middle line:84%
and I've had a few experiences
where I could see the crossover.

00:37:47.360 --> 00:37:52.340 align:middle line:84%
I had one patient who seemed
to be on a different level,

00:37:52.340 --> 00:37:53.760 align:middle line:90%
and he was actively dying.

00:37:53.760 --> 00:37:58.190 align:middle line:84%
And I walked into the room
and he said, oh, John, this

00:37:58.190 --> 00:37:59.610 align:middle line:90%
is my nurse, Penny.

00:37:59.610 --> 00:38:01.610 align:middle line:84%
And I immediately
was like, what?

00:38:01.610 --> 00:38:02.940 align:middle line:90%
He's hallucinating.

00:38:02.940 --> 00:38:05.240 align:middle line:84%
And I realized immediately
he was talking to somebody

00:38:05.240 --> 00:38:06.230 align:middle line:90%
who had already passed.

00:38:06.230 --> 00:38:09.130 align:middle line:84%
And, oh, I'm sorry, I said,
do you guys need a minute?

00:38:09.130 --> 00:38:11.130 align:middle line:84%
Because I was going in
the room to do something.

00:38:11.130 --> 00:38:13.260 align:middle line:84%
And he's like, no,
no, come in, sit down.

00:38:13.260 --> 00:38:14.490 align:middle line:90%
This is my brother, John.

00:38:14.490 --> 00:38:17.250 align:middle line:84%
And I said, are you going to
be leaving with John soon?

00:38:17.250 --> 00:38:19.290 align:middle line:84%
And he said, yeah, I
think John came to get me.

00:38:19.290 --> 00:38:20.760 align:middle line:90%
I think we will be leaving soon.

00:38:20.760 --> 00:38:23.900 align:middle line:90%
And he passed the next day.

00:38:23.900 --> 00:38:26.720 align:middle line:84%
So I've seen some of
those situations, where

00:38:26.720 --> 00:38:30.380 align:middle line:84%
their doctors will write it
off to the medications or just

00:38:30.380 --> 00:38:33.060 align:middle line:90%
the dysfunction of a dying mind.

00:38:33.060 --> 00:38:36.890 align:middle line:84%
But to me, when I watch the
patients interact that way,

00:38:36.890 --> 00:38:38.480 align:middle line:84%
they're very lucid,
they're more lucid

00:38:38.480 --> 00:38:41.170 align:middle line:84%
than they were before they
started interacting that way.

00:38:41.170 --> 00:38:44.980 align:middle line:84%
They suddenly seem very sharp
and acute with their senses.

00:38:44.980 --> 00:38:47.220 align:middle line:84%
And he even told me
not to sit in the chair

00:38:47.220 --> 00:38:48.660 align:middle line:90%
that John was sitting in.

00:38:48.660 --> 00:38:51.210 align:middle line:84%
And I've had things like
that happen more than once,

00:38:51.210 --> 00:38:54.450 align:middle line:84%
where you can see this
transitionary space that they're

00:38:54.450 --> 00:38:58.380 align:middle line:84%
in before they
completely cross over.

00:38:58.380 --> 00:39:00.920 align:middle line:84%
>> That's what we call the
end of life experiences.

00:39:00.920 --> 00:39:05.920 align:middle line:10%
You have to know that they will
die and they can see light,

00:39:05.920 --> 00:39:09.120 align:middle line:10%
they can see deceased relatives,
like a deceased partner,

00:39:09.120 --> 00:39:11.920 align:middle line:10%
or deceased parents, or
deceased child as well.

00:39:11.920 --> 00:39:13.920 align:middle line:90%
Children will see angels.

00:39:13.920 --> 00:39:17.130 align:middle line:84%
And it happens just in
the hours, days, or weeks

00:39:17.130 --> 00:39:18.360 align:middle line:90%
before they die.

00:39:18.360 --> 00:39:19.607 align:middle line:90%
And they can talk about it.

00:39:19.607 --> 00:39:21.440 align:middle line:84%
The difference with a
near-death experience,

00:39:21.440 --> 00:39:22.690 align:middle line:90%
they are unconscious.

00:39:22.690 --> 00:39:24.780 align:middle line:84%
But when you have an
end of life experience,

00:39:24.780 --> 00:39:26.968 align:middle line:84%
you're in and out this
waking consciousness.

00:39:26.968 --> 00:39:29.260 align:middle line:84%
So they can tell about what
happens, and what they see,

00:39:29.260 --> 00:39:31.350 align:middle line:84%
and what they
experience as well.

00:39:31.350 --> 00:39:34.980 align:middle line:84%
We know from other studies
that presumably more than 80%

00:39:34.980 --> 00:39:38.100 align:middle line:84%
of people who are dying have
this kind of experiences,

00:39:38.100 --> 00:39:41.160 align:middle line:84%
but unfortunately, most of
these end of life experiences

00:39:41.160 --> 00:39:44.790 align:middle line:84%
are not recognized and
called an hallucination.

00:39:44.790 --> 00:39:46.650 align:middle line:84%
But also in other
circumstances, you

00:39:46.650 --> 00:39:50.490 align:middle line:84%
can have this kind of
experiences, existential crisis,

00:39:50.490 --> 00:39:54.420 align:middle line:90%
isolation, meditation.

00:39:54.420 --> 00:39:58.000 align:middle line:84%
>> After this happened to
me, I was praying so hard,

00:39:58.000 --> 00:40:03.710 align:middle line:84%
and so heavy every day to
please let me back in heaven,

00:40:03.710 --> 00:40:07.600 align:middle line:90%
to please let me back in heaven.

00:40:07.600 --> 00:40:10.480 align:middle line:84%
And every single
time the answer would

00:40:10.480 --> 00:40:13.600 align:middle line:84%
come, I know this is
going to be hard, Vinnie,

00:40:13.600 --> 00:40:15.540 align:middle line:90%
but it's going to be worth it.

00:40:15.540 --> 00:40:19.810 align:middle line:84%
And about eight weeks after my
experience, I met a real angel.

00:40:19.810 --> 00:40:20.940 align:middle line:90%
I met my wife.

00:40:20.940 --> 00:40:25.530 align:middle line:84%
And she helped me on my
transition of the old me

00:40:25.530 --> 00:40:27.540 align:middle line:90%
to becoming the new me.

00:40:27.540 --> 00:40:31.200 align:middle line:84%
She helped me into this
new era of my life,

00:40:31.200 --> 00:40:35.760 align:middle line:84%
where family matters, where
loving others matters,

00:40:35.760 --> 00:40:38.910 align:middle line:84%
where caring for
others is paramount.

00:40:38.910 --> 00:40:42.900 align:middle line:84%
So I died in January, came
back three days later.

00:40:42.900 --> 00:40:46.650 align:middle line:84%
And that following July,
I was engaged to my wife

00:40:46.650 --> 00:40:49.740 align:middle line:84%
and we went to a little
tiny town in Wyoming,

00:40:49.740 --> 00:40:51.730 align:middle line:90%
called Afton, Wyoming.

00:40:51.730 --> 00:40:53.290 align:middle line:90%
We're there at a family reunion.

00:40:53.290 --> 00:40:57.030 align:middle line:84%
We're seeing the history of the
town performed in front of us

00:40:57.030 --> 00:40:58.980 align:middle line:90%
at the local high school.

00:40:58.980 --> 00:41:03.130 align:middle line:10%
And we're watching the men and
women who created this town,

00:41:03.130 --> 00:41:05.710 align:middle line:10%
they're showing pictures
of different people.

00:41:05.710 --> 00:41:09.390 align:middle line:84%
My wife looked over and
she said, that's him.

00:41:09.390 --> 00:41:13.740 align:middle line:84%
I had described Drake, my
guide, so many times to her

00:41:13.740 --> 00:41:16.460 align:middle line:84%
that she felt she
really knew who he was.

00:41:16.460 --> 00:41:20.410 align:middle line:84%
And she saw this picture come
up on the screen and she said,

00:41:20.410 --> 00:41:21.460 align:middle line:90%
that's him.

00:41:21.460 --> 00:41:25.090 align:middle line:84%
And I recognized
absolutely it was him.

00:41:25.090 --> 00:41:27.970 align:middle line:84%
There was no
question it was him.

00:41:27.970 --> 00:41:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And it helped solidify
that it really

00:41:31.060 --> 00:41:35.420 align:middle line:84%
did happen because me being
who I am, I'm very analytical,

00:41:35.420 --> 00:41:38.110 align:middle line:84%
and I was starting to
believe some of the stories

00:41:38.110 --> 00:41:39.970 align:middle line:84%
that neurologists
tried to tell me,

00:41:39.970 --> 00:41:44.950 align:middle line:84%
that a lot of these experiences
are just delusions made up

00:41:44.950 --> 00:41:47.770 align:middle line:84%
in our imagination,
and it's just the brain

00:41:47.770 --> 00:41:49.780 align:middle line:90%
trying to fill in the gaps.

00:41:49.780 --> 00:41:53.170 align:middle line:84%
But there's no
possible way for me

00:41:53.170 --> 00:41:55.810 align:middle line:84%
to make up a character
that really existed,

00:41:55.810 --> 00:41:58.450 align:middle line:84%
who I never met
before in my life.

00:41:58.450 --> 00:42:01.090 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I
got as a confirmation

00:42:01.090 --> 00:42:03.880 align:middle line:90%
that, yes, he was real.

00:42:03.880 --> 00:42:06.650 align:middle line:84%
So to me, Drake's
one of my angels.

00:42:06.650 --> 00:42:09.160 align:middle line:84%
He's one of my guides,
one of my protectors.

00:42:09.160 --> 00:42:12.370 align:middle line:84%
And months later, I
got the opportunity

00:42:12.370 --> 00:42:14.860 align:middle line:84%
to move in with my grandmother
to help take care of her

00:42:14.860 --> 00:42:16.280 align:middle line:90%
at the end of her life.

00:42:16.280 --> 00:42:19.150 align:middle line:84%
And while we were there, we were
going through some old paperwork

00:42:19.150 --> 00:42:20.030 align:middle line:90%
with her.

00:42:20.030 --> 00:42:23.810 align:middle line:84%
And we have one file
that says, "D. Cazier."

00:42:23.810 --> 00:42:27.940 align:middle line:10%
We open it up, and it's all
this stuff about Drake Cazier,

00:42:27.940 --> 00:42:32.500 align:middle line:10%
about my guide, who he was in
real life, and then about a page

00:42:32.500 --> 00:42:36.010 align:middle line:10%
to a page and a half of
all the important things he

00:42:36.010 --> 00:42:39.470 align:middle line:10%
was going to do after
this life, after he dies.

00:42:39.470 --> 00:42:42.940 align:middle line:84%
And one of the primary
duties he was going to embody

00:42:42.940 --> 00:42:47.080 align:middle line:84%
was to be a guide or an
escort to his family,

00:42:47.080 --> 00:42:52.000 align:middle line:84%
to his loved ones, and to anyone
who called out for his help.

00:42:52.000 --> 00:42:55.990 align:middle line:84%
So it was really a beautiful
kind of a third confirmation

00:42:55.990 --> 00:42:59.230 align:middle line:84%
for me that not
only was he real,

00:42:59.230 --> 00:43:01.990 align:middle line:84%
but he was fulfilling
a foretelling

00:43:01.990 --> 00:43:05.380 align:middle line:84%
of what his life purpose
was, not just in this world,

00:43:05.380 --> 00:43:06.516 align:middle line:90%
but in the eternities.

00:43:06.516 --> 00:43:09.550 align:middle line:90%


00:43:09.550 --> 00:43:12.820 align:middle line:84%
>> I think they can
see us if they want to.

00:43:12.820 --> 00:43:15.370 align:middle line:84%
When there are problems,
they will be there.

00:43:15.370 --> 00:43:20.080 align:middle line:84%
And the personality, the essence
of who we are is the same.

00:43:20.080 --> 00:43:24.320 align:middle line:84%
It's the ego with all the hate,
and the jealousy, whatever--

00:43:24.320 --> 00:43:25.880 align:middle line:90%
this is gone.

00:43:25.880 --> 00:43:29.330 align:middle line:84%
So the essence of who we
are, the personality traits,

00:43:29.330 --> 00:43:31.070 align:middle line:90%
are kept forever.

00:43:31.070 --> 00:43:33.920 align:middle line:84%
And it's become
one with everything

00:43:33.920 --> 00:43:36.200 align:middle line:90%
in the higher dimension.

00:43:36.200 --> 00:43:37.000 align:middle line:90%